    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Antal Verancsics (Augsburg, 23 October
                    1550)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Oláh has received two of Verancsics’s letters, which
                            have informed him better than any letter from other people. He is trying
                            to obtain the office of lector in Esztergom for Verancsics, and he will
                            receive the King’s deed from Georg Bona when he returns to Vienna from
                            Eger. He will send Máté Szerdahelyi in three days to look after the
                            affairs of the estate with Verancsics’s help.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">
                    <del corresp="author">Antonius Wrancius Nicolao Olaho salutem.</del>
                    <add corresp="author" type="corr">Nicolaus Olahus Antonio Wrancio suo
                        salutem!</add>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Binas tuas litteras accepi ante aliquot dies intra Septembrium et
                    Octobrium <milestone unit="pb"/>Kalendarum tempus ad me datas.<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We know five letters from Verancsics to Oláh
                        during September and October 1550: Ep. 745., Ep. 746., Ep. 747., Ep. 748.,
                        and Ep.
                        749.<ref>olahus.tei.15500902_1</ref></note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15500926_1</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15500928_1</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15501002_1</ref><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15501011_1</ref>
                    Habeo tibi magnas gratias, quod non praetermiseris me de his rebus facere
                    certiorem, quas ab aliis minus perspicue et copiose cognoveramus. Negotium
                    lectoratus Strigoniensis,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Verancsics aspired
                        to the <hi rend="italic">officium lectoratus</hi> of Esztergom, see Ep.
                            745.<ref>olahus.tei.15500902_1</ref></note> spero, quod brevi pro voto
                    tuo expediam, habes enim principem tibi benignissimum, me paterne affectum,
                    eiusque donationis litteras, cum
                        <placeName>Agria</placeName><placeName>Viennam</placeName> redieris,
                    invenies apud <placeName>Bonnam</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.3"
                        >Georg Bona.</note> meum sororium. Proinde mittam hoc triduo istuc
                        <persName>Matthaeum Zerdahelinum</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Máté Szerdahelyi was Provost of Myslina, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Pirhalla</hi> 1899, 220–221; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Erős</hi> 2018, 47–48.</note> secretarium meum in quibusdam rebus meis
                    peculiaribus, cui te in omnibus collegam assignavi, iussique, ut nihil prorsus
                    agat sine te et consilio tuo, quemadmodum ex eodem <persName>Matthaeo</persName>
                    et ex litteris meis, quas ei ad te dedi, intelliges. Tu itaque interim, dum
                        <milestone unit="pb"/><persName>Matthaeus</persName> advenit, tuas res <add
                        corresp="author" type="insert">familiares</add> istic componas, quo postea
                    confectis meis negotiis ad me remeare possis. Vale. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">23. Octobris 1550. <placeName>Augustae</placeName>. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
